The paper deals with semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves working with a database, which suggests a connection to cs.DB (Databases). The use of LSTM-based encoder-decoder architecture and attention mechanisms indicates a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves querying and searching for information, which is related to information retrieval (IR) and falls under the category of cs.IR.
